!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

pleased /pliːzd/

1. ADJ If you are pleased , you are happy about something or satisfied with something. 开心的 

例： Felicity seemed pleased at the suggestion. 费利西蒂似乎对这个建议很满意。 

例： I think he's going to be pleased that we identified the real problems. 我想他会为我们找到真正的问题所在高兴的。 

2. ADJ If you say you will be pleased to do something, you are saying in a polite way that you are willing to do it. 乐意 (做某事) 的 [v-link ADJ to-inf] [礼貌] 

例： We will be pleased to answer any questions you may have. 我们将愿意回答你可能有的任何问题。 

3. ADJ You can tell someone that you are pleased with something they have done in order to express your approval. 满意的 [v-link ADJ] [情感] 

例： I'm pleased with the way things have been going. 我对事情的进展状况感到满意。 

例： I am very pleased about the result. 我对结果很满意。 

例： We are pleased that the problems have been resolved. 我们很高兴问题已经得到了解决。 

4. ADJ When you are about to give someone some news that you know will please them, you can say that you are pleased to tell them the news or that they will be pleased to hear it. 高兴的 (告诉或听到消息) [v-link ADJ to-inf] 

例： I'm pleased to say that he is now doing well. 我很高兴地告诉你，他现在很好。 

5. ADJ In official letters, people often say they will be pleased to do something, as a polite way of introducing what they are going to do or inviting people to do something. 愿意的 (用于官方信函中礼貌地介绍打算要做的事或邀请人们做某事) [v-link ADJ to-inf] [礼貌] 

例： We will be pleased to delete the charge from the original invoice. 我们将愿意将这笔收费从原来的发票中删去。 

6. PHRASE If someone seems very satisfied with something they have done, you can say that they are pleased with themselves , especially if you think they are more satisfied than they should be. 洋洋自得 

例： 'Sophie was glad to see you,' he said, pleased with himself again for having remembered her name. “索菲很高兴见到你，”他说，为自己记住了她的名字又暗自得意。 

7. CONVENTION You can say ' Pleased to meet you ' as a polite way of greeting someone who you are meeting for the first time. 很高兴见到你 (用于初次见面问候对方) [套语]

